OL,6,FAs Judith Hamilton, 82, waved him off
OL,7,Fto the airport, she says her son told
OL,8,Fher: "He put his arms around me,
OL,9,Flooked me straight in the eyes and he
OL,10,Fwas smiling. And he said 'love you,
OL,11,Fmum, love you lots, always have,
OL,12,Falways will no matter what'."
OL,14,FThe chemistry teacher had dramatically
OL,15,Flost weight and complained of stomach
OL,16,Fproblems in the months leading up to
OL,17,Fhis death, but did not have a
OL,18,Fdiagnosed illness.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/18
