OL,6,FHowever, they also made clear that
OL,7,FPegasos does not believe in many of
OL,8,Fthe guidelines, which also state that
OL,9,Fa life should be unbearable before
OL,10,Fsomeone is assisted to die.
OL,12,FFollowing the meeting, Judith and
OL,13,FBradley told us that they were pleased
OL,14,FPegasos intended to tighten its
OL,15,Fprocedures, but still believe Alastair
OL,16,Fshould not have been allowed to die
OL,17,Fwithout their knowledge.
