OL,6,F"In 2022, the Swiss Medical
OL,7,FAssociation revised its guidelines
OL,8,Fregarding assisted dying. It is
OL,9,Fimportant to understand that these
OL,10,Fguidelines are not legally binding for
OL,11,Fthe associations but are policies for
OL,12,Fthe medical professionals. Several
OL,13,Forganisations for assisted dying,
OL,14,Fincluding Exit, Dignitas and Pegasos,
OL,15,Fpublicly spoke out against the revised
OL,16,Fguidelines, because they are putting
OL,17,Fat risk the self-determination of
OL,18,Fpeople planning a voluntary assisted
OL,19,Fdeath and the freedom of choice in
OL,20,FSwitzerland."
